Notably, Singapore-based Three Arrows Capital is the first qualified investor to hold more than 5% of GBTC shares. Davies told The Block that the fund has today <a href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1588489/000110465920072126/tm2022330d1_sc13g.htm" data-v-f87c67ca="">filed a Schedule 13G</a> form with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) for holding 6.26% of all shares in GBTC.&nbsp;<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
It is not clear whether Three Arrows Capital contributed “in-kind,” meaning whether it deposited its own bitcoins in exchange for GBTC shares. Davies declined to comment on the matter.&nbsp;
